Introduction:
HTML Response → The server sends an HTML page back to the client.
Status Code → Indicates whether the client’s request was successful or encountered an error.
 200 → OK (Success)
 404 → Not Found
 500 → Server Error
Eg:
| Concept | Node.js Example | Notes |
| ------------- | --------------------------------------------------------- | --------------------------------------- |
| HTML Response | res.write("<h1>Hello</h1>") | Send HTML page to browser 
|
| Status Code | res.writeHead(200) | 200 OK, 404 Not Found, 500 Server Error 
|
| JSON Response | res.writeHead(200, {"Content-Type":"application/json"}) | Send JSON data 
|
| End Response | res.end() | Finish sending data |